{
  "text": "DNA and RNA were extracted from 200 mg of leaf and flower tissue according to previously described protocols [CITATION_1] . PCR amplifications were performed with the Hot Star Taq Master kit (Qiagen). Thermocycling conditions were 958C for 10 min followed by 36 cycles of 948C for 15 s, 608C for 45 s, and 728C for 1 to 2 min. The purified PCR products were separated on 1.3% agarose gel and stained with ethidium bromide to verify that a single product in the expected length was amplified. PCR products were sequenced as described by [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "34061592",
